SIMPLE: whiskered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whiskered
<hw>Whisk"ered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed into whiskers; furnished with whiskers;
having or wearing whiskers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our forefathers, a grave, <qex>whiskered</qex> race.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having elongated hairs, feathers,
or bristles on the cheeks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>whiskered</qex> vermin race.</q>
<rj><qau>Grainger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whiskerless</ent>⟦br⟧
